  "prompt": "What makes a good gaming PC?",
  "response": "A good gaming PC typically consists of:\n\n1. Processor (CPU)\n- High performance multi-core processor\n- Intel Core i5/i7/i9 or AMD Ryzen 5/7/9\n- High clock speed and good single/multi-core performance\n\n2. Graphics Card (GPU)\n- NVIDIA GeForce RTX series or AMD Radeon RX series\n- More VRAM for better performance\n- Supports high refresh rates and resolution\n\n3. RAM\n- Minimum 16GB, preferably 32GB\n- DDR4 or DDR5\n- High speed (3200MHz+)\n\n4. Storage\n- SSD for faster loading times\n- NVMe M.2 preferred\n- At least 500GB-1TB capacity\n- Optional: Additional HDD for extra storage\n\n5. Cooling System\n- Good airflow\n- Quality CPU cooler\n- Multiple case fans\n- Potential liquid cooling for better performance\n\n6. Power Supply\n- 650W-850W\n- 80+ Gold certification\n- Reliable brand\n- Sufficient wattage for components\n\n7. Motherboard\n- Compatible with CPU socket\n- Good VRM for overclocking\n- Sufficient ports and connectivity\n\nAdditional considerations include case design, RGB lighting, and future upgradability.",
